{"artifact_links": ["https://simonwillison.net/2026/May/14/datasette-ip-rate-limit"], "author_or_org": null, "canonical_url": "https://simonwillison.net/2026/May/14/datasette-ip-rate-limit", "collection_method": "rss_atom", "confidence": "high", "content_hash": "96c575fc80665534", "dedup_key": "rss-guid:simonwillison-blog:https://simonwillison.net/2026/May/14/datasette-ip-rate-limit/#atom-everything", "event_id": "event_f719f39d55265bee", "evidence_type": "supported_fact", "excerpt": "<p><strong>Release:</strong> <a href=\"https://github.com/datasette/datasette-ip-rate-limit/releases/tag/0.1a0\">datasette-ip-rate-limit 0.1a0</a></p>\n        <p>The <a href=\"https://datasette.io/\">datasette.io</a> site was being hammered by poorly-behaved crawlers, so I had Codex (GPT-5.5 xhigh) build a configurable rate limiting plugin to block IPs that were hammering specific areas of the site too quickly.</p>\n<p>Here's <a href=\"https://github.com/simonw/datasette.io/blob/b6022bf9987661b94a26d3143028193a6cabfdcf/datasette.yml#L103-L116\">the production configuration</a> I'm using on that site for the new plugin:</p>\n<pre>  <span class=\"pl-ent\">datasette-ip-rate-limit</span>:\n    <span class=\"pl-ent\">header</span>: <span class=\"pl-s\">Fly-Client-IP</span>\n    <span class=\"pl-ent\">max_keys</span>: <span class=\"pl-c1\">10000</span>\n    <span class=\"pl-ent\">exempt_paths</span>:\n    - <span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">\"</span>/static/*<span class=\"pl-pds\">\"</span></span>\n    - <span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">\"</span>/-/turnstile*<span class=\"pl-pds\">\"</span></span>\n    <span class=\"pl-ent\">rules</span>:\n    - <span class=\"pl-ent\">name</span>: <span class=\"pl-s\">demo-database", "identifiers": {}, "inferred_entities": [], "item_type": "rss_atom_item", "novelty_score": 0.0, "published_at": "2026-05-14T04:10:23+00:00", "ranking_explanation": "", "raw_metadata": {}, "relevance_score": 0.0, "retrieved_at": "2026-05-14T22:27:09Z", "source_id": "simonwillison-blog", "source_name": "Simon Willison's Weblog", "source_native_id": "https://simonwillison.net/2026/May/14/datasette-ip-rate-limit/#atom-everything", "source_policy": "public_official", "source_type": "primary_artifact", "summary_hint": "<p><strong>Release:</strong> <a href=\"https://github.com/datasette/datasette-ip-rate-limit/releases/tag/0.1a0\">datasette-ip-rate-limit 0.1a0</a></p>\n        <p>The <a href=\"https://datasette.io/\">datasette.io</a> site was being hammered by poorly-behaved crawlers, so I had Codex (GPT-5.5 xhigh) build a configurable rate limiting plugin to block IPs that were hammering specific areas of the site too quickly.</p>\n<p>Here's <a href=\"https://github.com/simonw/datasette.io/blob/b6022bf9987661b94a26d3143028193a6cabfdcf/datasette.yml#L103-L116\">the production configuration</a> I'm using on that site for the new plugin:</p>\n<pre>  <span class=\"pl-ent\">datasette-ip-rate-limit</span>:\n    <span class=\"pl-ent\">header</span>: <span class=\"pl-s\">Fly-Client-IP</span>\n    <span class=\"pl-ent\">max_keys</span>: <span class=\"pl-c1\">10000</span>\n    <span class=\"pl-ent\">exempt_paths</span>:\n    - <span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">\"</span>/static/*<span class=\"pl-pds\">\"</span></span>\n    - <span class=\"pl-s\"><span class=\"pl-pds\">\"</span>/-/turnstile*<span class=\"pl-pds\">\"</span></span>\n    <span class=\"pl-ent\">rules</span>:\n    - <span class=\"pl-ent\">name</span>: <span class=\"pl-s\">demo-database", "title": "datasette-ip-rate-limit 0.1a0", "topics": ["topic_datasette-rate-limit-1a0"], "updated_at": null}
{"artifact_links": ["https://simonwillison.net/2026/May/13/welcome-to-the-datasette-blog"], "author_or_org": null, "canonical_url": "https://simonwillison.net/2026/May/13/welcome-to-the-datasette-blog", "collection_method": "rss_atom", "confidence": "high", "content_hash": "27eb77f9d6c87e2c", "dedup_key": "rss-guid:simonwillison-blog:https://simonwillison.net/2026/May/13/welcome-to-the-datasette-blog/#atom-everything", "event_id": "event_0b2e955636d7fbfd", "evidence_type": "supported_fact", "excerpt": "<p><strong><a href=\"https://datasette.io/blog/2026/new-blog/\">Welcome to the Datasette blog</a></strong></p>\nWe have a bunch of neat Datasette announcements in the pipeline so we decided it was time the project grew an official blog.</p>\n<p>I built this using OpenAI Codex desktop, which turns out to have the Markdown session transcript export feature I've always wanted. Here's <a href=\"https://gist.github.com/simonw/885b11eee46822622b8031a1f4e5f3a3\">the session that built the blog</a>. See also <a href=\"https://github.com/simonw/datasette.io/issues/179\">issue 179</a>.\n\n\n    <p>Tags: <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/ai\">ai</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/datasette\">datasette</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/generative-ai\">generative-ai</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/llms\">llms</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/ai-assisted-programming\">ai-assisted-programming</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/codex\">codex</a></p>", "identifiers": {}, "inferred_entities": [], "item_type": "rss_atom_item", "novelty_score": 0.0, "published_at": "2026-05-13T23:59:39+00:00", "ranking_explanation": "", "raw_metadata": {}, "relevance_score": 0.0, "retrieved_at": "2026-05-14T22:27:09Z", "source_id": "simonwillison-blog", "source_name": "Simon Willison's Weblog", "source_native_id": "https://simonwillison.net/2026/May/13/welcome-to-the-datasette-blog/#atom-everything", "source_policy": "public_official", "source_type": "primary_artifact", "summary_hint": "<p><strong><a href=\"https://datasette.io/blog/2026/new-blog/\">Welcome to the Datasette blog</a></strong></p>\nWe have a bunch of neat Datasette announcements in the pipeline so we decided it was time the project grew an official blog.</p>\n<p>I built this using OpenAI Codex desktop, which turns out to have the Markdown session transcript export feature I've always wanted. Here's <a href=\"https://gist.github.com/simonw/885b11eee46822622b8031a1f4e5f3a3\">the session that built the blog</a>. See also <a href=\"https://github.com/simonw/datasette.io/issues/179\">issue 179</a>.\n\n\n    <p>Tags: <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/ai\">ai</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/datasette\">datasette</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/generative-ai\">generative-ai</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/llms\">llms</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/ai-assisted-programming\">ai-assisted-programming</a>, <a href=\"https://simonwillison.net/tags/codex\">codex</a></p>", "title": "Welcome to the Datasette blog", "topics": ["topic_welcome-the-datasette-blog"], "updated_at": null}
